  "articleSummary": "The article argues that the real security problem on developer laptops is “blast‑radius”: anything that runs as the developer should not automatically inherit all of the user’s privileges. It proposes a four‑layer defense—Isolation, Secret handling, Detection, and Egress control—centered on practical, low‑friction tools such as dev‑containers (with minimal mounts), encrypted or managed .env files, and canary‑token monitoring. The tone is a pragmatic tutorial that mixes “enterprise wallpaper” and “survivalist” extremes, using the metaphor of a “blast radius” to frame the need for tighter boundaries without turning development into a slog. The intended audience is engineering teams and individual developers who want actionable, up‑to‑date guidance for hardening their workstations while preserving a smooth developer experience.",
